					<description><![CDATA[üíª Crypto Mining 101 + XMR vs RTM Deep Dive (2025 Edition) Ever wondered how crypto mining actually works, or which coin is best for your CPU rig? This unified guide breaks it down step-by-step‚Äîfrom beginner basics to an in-depth comparison of Monero (XMR) and Raptoreum (RTM). üîç What is Mining? Crypto mining is how decentralized coins are minted and secured. Miners validate transactions by solving mathematical puzzles using computing power. In return, they‚Äôre rewarded with crypto. ‚öôÔ∏è How It Works üß± Transactions are grouped into blocks. ‚öôÔ∏è Miners solve complex puzzles to validate the block. ‚úÖ The first miner to solve it adds the block to the chain. üí∏ They earn coins + transaction fees. üß† Types of Mining Hardware CPU: Best for XMR, RTM. Low power, low cost. GPU: Great for coins like RVN, ETHW. ASIC: Ultra-fast but costly and noisy. Best for BTC, LTC. FPGA: Rare, customizable, power-efficient. üí° What to Consider Before Mining üîå Electricity Cost: Cheap or free power makes a difference. üñ•Ô∏è Your Hardware: Old laptop? Server? Mini PC? üïµÔ∏è‚Äç‚ôÇÔ∏è Your Goals: Profit, privacy, or passive earning? üåê Network Difficulty: Is it beginner-friendly or competitive? üí∏ Rewards: Pool or solo? Auto payout or wallet-based? üî• XMR vs RTM ‚Äì Which Should You Mine? Comparing Monero and Raptoreum reveals key differences in privacy, power usage, setup, and rewards. üìú Algorithm &#038; Use Case XMR: Uses RandomX, optimized for CPUs. High privacy, ASIC-resistant. RTM: Uses GhostRider, a hybrid algorithm that randomly mixes hash functions. Lighter on power, flexible. üí∞ Profitability &#038; Difficulty XMR has strong price stability and global demand‚Äîbut it‚Äôs competitive. RTM offers higher yields per hash on average due to lower network difficulty. ‚öôÔ∏è Sample Configurations Example XMRig config for XMR: { "algo": "rx/0", "pools": [{ "url": "pool.supportxmr.com:3333", "user": "YOUR_XMR_WALLET", "pass": "x" }] } RTM using cpuminer-opt (GhostRider algo): ./cpuminer --algo ghostrider -o stratum+tcp://stratum.rplant.xyz:17022 -u YOUR_RTM_WALLET üîê Privacy &#038; Purpose XMR: A true privacy coin. Untraceable transactions, strong community. RTM: Focuses on utility‚Äîsupports nodes, dApps, and digital assets. üîß Use Case Scenarios Private Browsing &#038; Payments: XMR is ideal. Passive Income on Old PCs: RTM wins here. Multi-coin Efficiency: Use both on hybrid rigs. üöÄ Bonus Tip: Multi-Coin CPU Mining Divide your CPU threads to run both XMR and RTM miners in parallel. Optimize based on temperature and hashrate. For full tutorial, check out our Multi-Coin Rig Guide. ‚úÖ Final Thoughts Don‚Äôt just mine what‚Äôs trending. Mine what aligns with your values and resources. Whether you prefer XMR‚Äôs rock-solid privacy or RTM‚Äôs utility and potential, both are excellent choices for low-power mining in 2025.]]></description>
